				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Both addresses in $8000-$BFFF and addresses in $C000-$FFFF work. But for one thing, DMC assumes $C000-$FFFF. And for another, it's traditional to use $C000-$FFFF.<br /><br />Advanced: Say you're making a multicart of NROM-128 games. For some common boards, either they must all be in $8000-$BFFF (if UNROM configured as mapper 2) or  they must all be in $C000-$FFFF (if UNROM configured as mapper 180). But for other mappers, mixing the two can be advantageous.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

