				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You should note that the start address in the memory section do not matter for how the ROM file is output (sizes do). Start address only tell the linker the offset in ROM for things like absolute addresses. For example, your start address for the ROMV is wrong, it should be $FFF4, but it doesn't matter since there is no code in the segment. (Ignoring the mistake that the vectors start at $FFFA).</div>

